County Health Executive Gladys Kimingi said that in order to contain the spread of the virus, continuous sensitisation in schools as well as monitoring to ensure that the laid-down guidelines are followed will be carried out.
This will complement the campaigns that were carried out in schools following last term’s partial re-opening.
Ms Kimingi said that so far, about 200 teachers have been reached while students from about 60 schools have been sensitised in the past one month when the Department of Health embarked on accelerated Covid-19 prevention campaigns around the county.



