She added that the county government has linked all the schools with health workers who will be in contact with them from time to time, offering the required guidance as well as ensuring that they follow the guidelines issued by the Ministry of Health which include wearing of masks and washing of hands, among others.
Apart from sensitising teachers and students, roles of other staff in the schools such as watchmen, cooks and groundsmen have been spelt out so that they all play their part in the prevention of Covid-19 spread in the schools.
She stressed that the Health Department has also come up with a reporting template for Covid-19 suspected cases in schools which is supposed to be filled in by school heads and submitted to the sub-county Covid-19 multi-agency team through the sub-county public health officers. The template captures details of students, the symptoms exhibited and the facility they are referred to.



