The county has also constructed an additional 20 classrooms and two dormitories to expand the capacity of the youth polytechnics in the last three years.
Mr Kinyua also said that pupils from ECDE centres will benefit from free face masks from a consignment of 140,000 masks set to be distributed by the county government to school children.
The masks are produced by the Department of Gender at the county’s Kaitheri Apparel Factory in Kerugoya.
He urged school staff, parents and pupils to play their part in preventing the spread of the virus, both while in school and outside.
Kirinyaga County has so far recorded a total of 476 positive Covid-19 cases and seven deaths. A total of 21 patients have so far recovered and been discharged from isolation centres while others have recovered while under the home-based care programme.
Currently, there is no patient admitted at the county’s isolation centre while four are recovering under home-based care. Death toll in the country from the pandemic now stands at 1,702 after eight fatalities were reported in the last 24 hours. Four more patients succumb to Covid-19 in the last 24 hours pushing cumulative fatalities to 1,690, Health ministry says. Judge allows withdrawal of petition that had blocked Ms Ann Mwenda from being vetted. The ICC has the authority to hear cases of war crimes, genocide and crimes against humanity committed in the 123 countries, including Uganda. In December, TSC failed to attend a negotiation meeting called by Labour CS Simon Chelugui to mediate the two parties.